	<article class="post-89076 post type-post status-publish hentry category-dashboard tag-small-business des-small-business news_keywords-small-business-2" id="post-89076">
	<header class="postHeader">
				<div class="postKicker">
					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Hiring Picks Up</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-10-03T15:18:26+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">October 3, 2014 11:18 am</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">October 3, 2014 11:18 am</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/10/03/today-in-small-business-hiring-picks-up/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Hiring Picks Up" data-description="The marketplace for local services is booming. Good news for owners hoping to sell a small business. And the economic case for paternity leave.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The jobless rate falls<a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/10/04/business/economy/monthly-jobs-report-september.html"> below 6 percent</a> for the first time since 2008.</li>
<li>New orders for manufactured goods <a href="//www.census.gov/manufacturing/m3/prel/pdf/s-i-o.pdf">were down</a> in August.</li>
<li>Data suggest American corporations are the <a href="//www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-10-02/corporate-u-s-healthiest-in-decades-under-obama-with-lower-debt.html">healthiest they have been</a> in decades.</li>
<li>Global economic growth <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/10/02/global-economic-growth-keeps-getting-downgraded/">keeps getting</a> downgraded.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>More owners of small and midsize businesses <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/orlando/blog/2014/10/more-small-business-owners-planning-pay-raises-and.html">plan to raise</a> salaries and prices, according to a new survey.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Selling the Business</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Thereâs good news for owners <a href="//www.inc.com/bob-house/good-news-for-sellers-hoping-to-exit-their-small-business.html">hoping to sell</a> a small business.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Opportunities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The marketplace for <a href="//www.smallbizlabs.com/2014/10/local-services-online-marketplaces-booming.html">local services</a> is booming.</li>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"> <span id="more-89076"></span>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Businesses tapping into <a href="//www.marketwired.com/press-release/witness-freelance-economys-rise-elance-odesk-releases-q3-2014-online-work-reports-1953020.htm">freelance talent</a> through the Internet have spent nearly $3 billion on Elance and oDesk.</li>
<li>Here is the <a href="//www.theatlantic.com/business/archive/2014/09/the-economic-case-for-paternity-leave/380716/?single_page=true">economic case</a> for paternity leave.</li>
<li>Minimum-wage workers could <a href="//blogs.wsj.com/economics/2014/10/02/minimum-wage-workers-could-see-big-raises-in-chicago-l-a-n-y-s-f/?Healthcare">see raises</a> in Chicago, L.A., N.Y., and S.F.</li>
<li>The Labor Department <a href="//www.usnews.com/news/business/articles/2014/10/01/us-issues-final-minimum-wage-rule-for-contractors">finalizes its raise</a> of the minimum wage to $10.10 for workers with federal contracts.</li>
<li>Apple unveils <a href="//fortune.com/2014/10/02/apple-employee-perks/">new perks</a> to attract talent.</li>
<li>Air Canada pilots are warned to <a href="//consumerist.com/2014/10/02/air-canada-pilots-warned-to-stop-sneaking-porn-into-the-cockpit-because-seriously/">stop sneaking porn</a> into the cockpit.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health Care</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A business owner tries to figure out whether his plan is &#8220;<a href="//m.wsj.com/articles/bosses-face-affordable-care-act-deadline-1412202286?mobile=y&amp;mg=reno64-wsj">affordable</a>,&#8221; as required by the Affordable Care Act.</li>
<li>Facebook <a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/10/03/us-facebook-health-idUSKCN0HS09720141003">may be getting</a> into the health care business.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Washington</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Small Business Administration is <a href="//www.kansas.com/news/business/small-business/article2480443.html">taking nominations</a> for its small-business awards.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>These 12 subject-line tweaks <a href="//blogs.constantcontact.com/product-blogs/email-marketing/subject-line-examples/?u">will improve</a> your email open rate.</li>
<li>Here is how <a href="//blog.crowdspring.com/2014/10/how-color-influences-what-people-buy/">color influences</a> what people buy.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Start-Up</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>And here&#8217;s how <a href="//www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20141001/park-slope/heres-how-much-it-costs-start-tiny-food-cart-business">much it costs to</a> start a food stand business.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Retail</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>An investor explains <a href="//seekingalpha.com/article/2537115-heres-why-ross-stores-is-so-good-at-making-money">why Ross Stores</a> is so good at making money.</li>
<li>This is why <a href="//www.businessinsider.com/why-chipotle-doesnt-franchise-2014-10">Chipotle doesnât franchise</a>.</li>
<li>A guy whoâs been to <a href="//consumerist.com/2014/10/02/guy-whos-been-to-11000-starbucks-outlets-would-rather-get-his-coffee-elsewhere/">11,000 Starbucks outlets</a> would rather get his coffee elsewhere.</li>
<li>UPS <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/morning_call/2014/10/ups-wants-retailers-to-stop-encouraging-last.html">wants retailers</a> to stop encouraging last-minute Christmas deliveries.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Finance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="//recode.net/2014/10/01/kickstarter-founders-next-project-will-crowdfund-nonprofits-with-a-dollar-a-day/">next project</a> for the founder of Kickstarter will be to crowdfund nonprofits.</li>
<li>If you had $2.5 trillion and 15 years to spend it, how would <a href="//freakonomics.com/2014/10/02/fixing-the-world-bang-for-the-buck-edition-a-new-freakonomics-radio-podcast/">you distribute the money</a> to achieve the most good?</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Data Security<br />
</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A <a href="//www.theguardian.com/business/2014/oct/02/jp-morgan-76m-households-affected-data-breach">data breach</a> at JP Morgan Chase exposes 76 million households.</li>
<li>A celebrity lawyer <a href="//time.com/3456003/google-lawsuit-nude-selfies/">threatens Google</a> with a $100 million lawsuit over nude selfies.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Social Media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Hereâs how to <a href="//www.ducttapemarketing.com/blog/2014/10/02/lifelong-follower/">turn a new fan</a> into a lifelong follower.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Public money <a href="//www.wesh.com/public-money-may-help-business-owners-in-daytona-beach/28361586">may help</a> business ownersÂ affected by construction in Daytona Beach, Fla.</li>
<li>Entrepreneurs in Ypsilanti, Mich. will have an opportunity <a href="//www.heritage.com/articles/2014/10/02/ypsilanti_courier/news/doc542af4397ec65260921237.txt">to test their business idea</a> with a new pop-up business program.</li>
<li>New Yorkâs governor has set a <a href="//www.newsday.com/business/cuomo-seeks-minority-women-businesses-on-30-percent-of-state-contracts-1.9456080">new state goal</a> of awarding 30 percent of government contracts to minority and women-owned businesses.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Ebola outbreak <a href="//americasmarkets.usatoday.com/2014/10/02/ebola-outbreak-disrupts-exxons-oil-drilling/">disrupts</a> Exxon&#8217;s oil drilling.</li>
<li>The biggest payday lender in Britain, under fire from regulators, is <a href="//money.cnn.com/2014/10/02/pf/payday-debt-wonga/index.html">forgiving more than</a> $350 million worth of consumer debt.</li>
<li>Around the world, 4.4 billion people <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2014/10/02/4-4-billion-people-around-the-world-still-dont-have-internet-heres-where-they-live/">still donât have</a> Internet.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Apple&#8217;s <a href="//readwrite.com/2014/10/02/apple-health-app">health app</a> is an embarrassment, according to a technology writer.</li>
<li>Eighty percent of small-business owners are <a href="//www.marketwired.com/press-release/-1952864.htm">employing mobile</a> technology for work, according to a new survey.</li>
<li>A flaw in <a href="//www.wired.com/2014/10/code-published-for-unfixable-usb-attack/">most USB drives</a> exposes data to hackers.</li>
</ul>
